# Changelog Maintenance

`CHANGELOG.md` at the repo root tracks notable changes. Keep it in sync with the code.

## When to update

Add an entry for any change that affects users:

- New features or `EnvConfig` fields
- API renames or removals (`make_env`, output field names, etc.)
- New or removed environments (`Procedural-FrozenLake-v1`, `SyntheticEnv-v1`, …)
- Changes to output/metric format or reward behavior
- Bug fixes that change observable behavior

## When NOT to update

Skip the changelog for:

- Internal refactors with no observable effect
- Test-only changes
- Doc typo fixes (no behavior change)

## Format

Always add to `## [Unreleased]` — never edit a released version block.
Use these sub-sections (omit any that don't apply):

```markdown
## [Unreleased]

### Added
- ...

### Changed
- ...

### Removed
- ...

### Fixed
- ...
```

## On version bump

When `version` in `pyproject.toml` is changed, promote `[Unreleased]` to the new version with today's date:

```markdown
## [x.y.z] - YYYY-MM-DD
```

Leave a fresh empty `## [Unreleased]` above it.
